2. ROOT CAUSE ANALYSIS — ChocoPhlAn DB missing on workers
================================================================================

### Symptom

All recent pipeline runs (5+ attempts on 2026-04-26, between 02:58–03:57 UTC)
failed at `profile_function` (HUMAnN4) with:

  CRITICAL ERROR: The directory provided for the ChocoPhlAn database at
  /mnt/dbs/chocophlan_v4_alpha/ does not exist.

Everything upstream succeeded: AWS_DOWNLOAD, FASTERQ_DUMP, count_reads,
clean_reads all completed in seconds. MetaPhlAn (profile_taxa) was either
killed by NF (pipeline abort after HUMAnN failure) or ran successfully
(its DB was present).

### Samples used

  SRR6664374, SRR6664342 (CHILD cohort, from samplesheet-smoke-child.csv)

### Failed Batch jobs (from CloudWatch /aws/batch/job)

  nf-barbarahelena-humann-4-0-3/default/6092d433... → exit 1, 6s
    "ChocoPhlAn database at /mnt/dbs/chocophlan_v4_alpha/ does not exist"

  nf-barbarahelena-humann-4-0-3/default/97c7493b... → exit 1, 6s
    Same error.

### Timeline of most recent run (03:52–03:57 UTC)

  03:52:39  get_software_versions submitted
  03:53:01  get_software_versions started (22s to start → worker pre-warmed)
  03:54:23  AWS_DOWNLOAD SRR6664374 started
  03:55:58  profile_function SRR6664342 submitted
  03:57:03  profile_function SRR6664342 started → FAILED in 6s
  03:57:08  Pipeline aborted, 3 tasks killed

### Root cause: ECS agent race condition

The Launch Template UserData does:
  1. Install miniconda (~3-5 min)
  2. Install awscli via conda (~1-3 min)
  3. S3 sync ~65 GiB / 30,124 objects from s3://cjb-gutz-s3-demo → /mnt/dbs/
  4. systemctl restart ecs

But on the AL2023 ECS-optimized AMI, the ECS agent starts automatically on
boot via systemd. It registers with the Batch cluster BEFORE the UserData
script runs (cloud-init final stage runs after services start). So:

  Boot → ECS agent starts → registers with Batch → JOBS ARRIVE
    ... meanwhile ...
  cloud-init final → UserData starts → miniconda install → S3 sync (15-60 min)
    → systemctl restart ecs (too late)

The S3 sync order explains why MetaPhlAn worked but HUMAnN didn't:
  - metaphlan_databases/: 9 files, 19.2 GiB → syncs fast
  - chocophlan_v4_alpha/: 30,094 files, 41.7 GiB → syncs last

### DB sizes in s3://cjb-gutz-s3-demo/

  metaphlan_databases/                    9 files    19.2 GiB
  chocophlan_v4_alpha/                30,094 files   41.7 GiB
  uniref90_annotated_v4_alpha.../         1 file      1.6 GiB
  full_mapping_v4_alpha/                 20 files     2.7 GiB
  Total (excl referencedata):       ~30,124 files   ~65.2 GiB

### Infrastructure state checked

  Stack: nf-reads-profiler-batch — deployed, parameters correct
  CEs: SpotComputeEnvironment (ENABLED/VALID), OnDemandComputeEnvironment (ENABLED/VALID)
  Launch template: lt-0d9193dd0f66d68ee — correct AMI (ami-02d671abb319baa35,
    al2023-ami-ecs-hvm-2023.0.20260414-kernel-6.1-arm64), correct UserData
  EcsInstanceRole: S3 access to cjb-gutz-s3-demo confirmed in IAM policy
  Instance profile: nf-reads-profiler-ecs-instance-profile attached to both CEs
  Running instances: 1 (i-0c85d6ecbdb08bac8) — this is the HEAD NODE (runner VM),
    not a Batch worker. Uses head-node-role, stock Ubuntu 24.04 AMI. No SSM agent.

================================================================================
3. FIX — Stop ECS before sync, start after
================================================================================

### Change: infra/batch-stack.yaml UserData

Before:
  #!/bin/bash
  ...
  aws s3 sync s3://${DbSourceBucket} /mnt/dbs/ --exclude "referencedata/*" --quiet
  systemctl restart ecs

After:
  #!/bin/bash
  ...
  systemctl stop ecs      # ← NEW: prevent jobs before sync
  ...
  aws s3 sync s3://${DbSourceBucket} /mnt/dbs/ --exclude "referencedata/*" --quiet
  systemctl start ecs     # ← CHANGED: start (not restart)

### Change: infra/readme.md

  - Updated "Database placement" section with accurate sizes (65 GiB, 30k objects)
    and documented the stop/start ECS pattern.
  - Added troubleshooting entry: "Fix: HUMAnN ChocoPhlAn database does not exist"
    with symptom, cause, fix, and verification steps.

### Change: CLAUDE.md

  - Fixed stale nreads value (33,333,333 → 32,000,000)
  - Replaced outdated EFS note with stop/start ECS description
  - Added debugging workflow section

### Deployment required

Stack must be redeployed to pick up the UserData change:
  aws cloudformation deploy ... (see infra/readme.md or /deploy-stack skill)
Then disable/re-enable CEs so new workers get the updated launch template.

